              <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA10000-A-06RT9-00131-A-001-01" />
            </figure>
            <para>As you know, a bike's brake system is used to slow down and stop the bike. Without this system, riding could be dangerous. </para>
            <para>There are many types of brake systems, and each is composed of several small parts. In this topic, you reviewed information regarding the main parts of the cantilever brake system. Cantilever brakes are considered to be the most common on modern bikes. Your bike's brake system, however, may look different, but they all work basically the same. </para>
            <para>Now that you have completed this topic, you should be able to identify a bike's brake system components.</para>
          </description>
        </lcSummary>
      </learningSummary>
    </learning>
